# Line-ending policy: LF everywhere, in the index AND the working tree, on every
# platform. The explicit catch-all overrides each clone's core.autocrlf, so checkouts
# are deterministic and tools that write LF never trigger conversion warnings.
# (text=auto leaves auto-detected binaries alone.)
*           text=auto eol=lf

# POSIX shell scripts and the `./taskkling` launcher MUST stay LF: a CRLF byte in a
# `#!/bin/sh` shebang breaks the interpreter, and `curl | sh` runs install.sh under
# /bin/sh regardless of the checkout. (Covered by the catch-all; kept explicit.)
*.sh        text eol=lf
/taskkling  text eol=lf

# Windows-only scripts keep CRLF (cmd.exe batch parsing has LF edge cases).
*.cmd       text eol=crlf
*.bat       text eol=crlf
*.ps1       text eol=crlf
